<body>
  <h1>Axon Privacy Policy</h1>

  <h2>1. Information Collection and Use</h2>
  <p>Axon does not collect any personal information. As an AI-based Chrome extension designed to provide intelligent conversation and assistance, Prismo may process the following data:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>User queries and conversation history (stored locally)</li>
    <li>Current webpage content (only for providing context-relevant assistance)</li>
    <li>User preferences (stored locally)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We use this information solely to improve user experience and provide personalized AI assistance.</p>

  <h2>2. Data Storage</h2>
  <p>All user data is stored exclusively on the user's local device. We do not store any information, personal or otherwise, on our servers.</p>

  <h2>3. Data Transmission</h2>
  <p>To provide AI assistance, we need to send user queries to your selected AI service providers (such as OpenAI, Anthropic). These queries do not contain any personal identifying information.</p>

  <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>We use third-party AI services to process user queries. These services have their own privacy policies, and we encourage users to review these policies to understand how they handle data.</p>

  <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
  <p>We implement appropriate security measures to protect user data from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure,